I"<h2 id="expressions">Expressions</h2>

<ol>
  <li>
    <p>They had agreed upon a <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="a symbolic fee of one peso"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(1比索象征性的收费)</code></b> fee of one peso, which she did not take and he did not hand to her, but which they put in the <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="piggy bank"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(小猪存钱罐)</code></b> until enough of them had accumulated to buy something charming from overseas in the Arcade of the Scribes.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>He had the <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="awful presentiment"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(强烈的预感)</code></b> that they were going to take many Sunday siestas together.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>But she <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="had the inclination of an alley cat"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(有着野猫似的不安分的天性)</code></b>, which were more indomitable than the strength of her tenderness, and this meant that both of them were condemned to infidelity.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>He considered it <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="a stroke of good fortune"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(一件幸运的事)</code></b> that among so many hazardous encounters, the only woman who had made him taste a drop of bitterness was the sinuous Sara Noriega.</p>
  </li>
</ol>
